    • move

      public GameControllerState move​(int workerRow, int workerColumn, int moveRow, int moveColumn, Model gd) throws NotAdjacentCellException, IncorrectLevelException, OccupiedCellException, DomedCellException, DivinityPowerException, NoTurnEndException
      Process the move. Artemis allows a second move, but not on the previous cell
      Overrides:
      move in class Divinity
      Parameters:
      workerRow - the row of the cell where the worker is
      workerColumn - the column of the cell where the worker is
      moveRow - the row of the board where the worker wants to move
      moveColumn - the column of the board where the worker wants to move
      gd - the game status
      Returns:
      the next method to be invoked by the controller
      Throws:
      NotAdjacentCellException - if the destination cell is not adjacent to the worker
      IncorrectLevelException - if the destination cell is too high to be reached
      OccupiedCellException - if the destination cell has another worker on it
      DomedCellException - if the destination cell has a dome on it
      DivinityPowerException - if the move isn't allowed by another divinity
      NoTurnEndException - if the move doesn't allow the player to end the turn
